That's exactly how I use my Powerbook (inherited from son) - the
screen is busted, so I have an external monitor, keyboard and mouse
attached. With most Mac laptops, as soon as you attach the external
peripherals, you can use it with the lid closed.

I've Â never tried it with my work supplied R51 but I wonder if it
works the same way. If you can attach an external keyboard, mouse and
monitor to your T42 you might want to see if it works the same way.

